{
  "_id": "96117070798788cf",
  "name": "UtI 1 — Vanishing Act",
  "pages": [
    {
      "_id": "133f1b510040e616",
      "name": "Read to the Players",
      "type": "text",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "\n        <p>Captain Burns looks unhappy today. He always looks unhappy — but today, even more so, and the fact that he's called you into his office this particular morning suggests whatever he has to say will make <em>you</em> unhappy too. He waves you to sit (there are two chairs, and he's in one of them), looks you over a long moment, and finally opens his mouth.</p>\n        <p>The job: one of the department's undercover people has gone dark, and the brass wants him found — quietly.</p>"
      },
      "system": {},
      "sort": 0,
      "ownership": {
        "default": -1
      },
      "flags": {},
